This paper deals with the problem of K-Nearest Neighbor (KNN) queries in multi-dimensional space, which is a common problem in databases and information retrieval. Therefore, cs.DB and cs.IR are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also proposes an algorithm for producing diverse result sets, which involves machine learning and optimization techniques, making cs.AI a likely sub-category as well. The paper also involves analyzing and evaluating the algorithm's performance on real and synthetic data, which falls under cs.DS and cs.LG.
